Hi Team,

The Kafka Console for the **dev-kafka** environment is now fully operational and available for monitoring and validation.

🔗 **Console URL:**
http://dev-kafkaconsole.apps.dev.sbiepay.sbi

You can use this console to:

* Monitor **Kafka cluster health** (CPU, Memory, Disk usage)
* View **topic-level metrics** (incoming/outgoing throughput)
* Check **consumer group details** (lag, offsets)
* Browse **topics, partitions, and messages**
* Validate application-level Kafka integrations

**Important Notes:**

* This is a **read-only monitoring interface**
* Access is restricted within the OpenShift network
* Metrics are near real-time and depend on application activity

We request all application teams to:

* Validate their topics and consumer groups
* Monitor message flow during testing
* Report any discrepancies or issues

For detailed usage and troubleshooting, please refer to the shared SOP.

If you face any issues accessing the console or observing metrics, please reach out to the DevOps/Kafka team.

